headline: GE Aerospace Partner Safran Rises On Rosy Guidance For 2026 And Beyond
summary: GE Aerospace's partner Safran raised its guidance for 2026 and beyond, forecasting growth of 10% for the next two years.

headline: General Dynamics Paid Investors $1.50: Here’s What the Dividend Reveals

headline: Boeing’s Strong January Orders Confront Labor Strains And Defense Demands
summary: Boeing (NYSE:BA) reports one of its strongest Januarys for aircraft orders and deliveries. The company outpaces Airbus in both new orders and deliveries for the month. Boeing secures a major U.S. Air Force contract to upgrade the C-17A transport aircraft fleet. Union groups raise concerns about job relocations to South Carolina and potential layoffs.
